 193:Display/../../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/hid/disp/display.h **** /** This class is intended as a intermediary class for your actual implementation of the OneBitGrap
 194:Display/../../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/hid/disp/display.h ****  *  interface. It uses the CRTP design pattern where the template argument is the child class. It p
 195:Display/../../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/hid/disp/display.h ****  *  implementations for most of the functions, except DrawPixel(), Update() and Fill(), which you'l
 196:Display/../../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/hid/disp/display.h ****  *  to provide in your child class.
 197:Display/../../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/hid/disp/display.h ****  *  The main goal of this class is to provide common drawing functions without relying on massive a
 198:Display/../../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/hid/disp/display.h ****  *  virtual function calls that would result in a performance loss. To achieve this, any drawing fu
 199:Display/../../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/hid/disp/display.h ****  *  is implemented here and internally calls other drawing functions (e.g. DrawRect() which interna
 200:Display/../../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/hid/disp/display.h ****  *  DrawPixel() and DrawLine()) makes these calls via the qualified name of these functions to expl
 201:Display/../../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/hid/disp/display.h ****  *  suppress the virtual dispatch mechanism like this:
 202:Display/../../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/hid/disp/display.h ****  * 
 203:Display/../../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/hid/disp/display.h ****  *      ChildType::DrawPixel(...); // no virtual function call; direct call into the child class fu
 204:Display/../../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/hid/disp/display.h ****  *  
 205:Display/../../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/hid/disp/display.h ****  *  To create a custom OneBitGraphicsDisplay implementation, you can 
 206:Display/../../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/hid/disp/display.h ****  *  A) inherit from OneBitGraphicsDisplay directly and provide all the drawing functions yourself
 207:Display/../../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/hid/disp/display.h ****  *  B) Inherit from OneBitGraphicsDisplayImpl and only provide DrawPixel(), Fill() and Update()
 208:Display/../../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/hid/disp/display.h ****  *     like this:
 209:Display/../../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/hid/disp/display.h ****  *  
 210:Display/../../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/hid/disp/display.h ****  *      class MyDisplayClass : public OneBitGraphicsDisplayImpl<MyDisplayClass> 
 211:Display/../../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/hid/disp/display.h ****  *      {
